answers.answer: It's an increase in growth, growth spurts are fairly common all the way through pregnancy, if you're measuring consistantly ahead you may have gotten the wrong due date, your baby might be a big baby, or you might have gestational diabetes, at this stage babies grow at all different rates so I wouldn't stress about it!
